AGI - US Vice President JD Vance is planning a visit to Italy for the end of April. Bloomberg reports it, specifying that Vance could go to Rome between 18 and 20 April > and that Washington diplomats asked Italian counterparts to organize a meeting with Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni>.&nbsp;
The official visit arrives on the wave of good relations with Rome. Ten days ago Vance had a telephone conversation with the deputypremier and leader of the League Matteo Salvini. During the interview, lasting fifteen minutes, the two leaders discussed cooperation between Italy and the United States, focusing on infrastructure, satellite communication and international security.
Vance expressed his appreciation for the Italian hospitality reserved to his wife, Usha, during his visit with his son at the Special Olympics in Turin, and manifested his intention to visit Italy soon. That moment is here. If confirmed, it will not be the only chance. Vance received an invitation to participate in the Winter Olympics in Milan-Cortina 2026>, extended by Salvini during their conversation.
This call, according to Rome and Washington, represents an opportunity to further strengthen the links between the two countries, at a time of global tension, between duties, expansionist duties and conflicts between Russia and Ukraine and the Middle East.' The visit takes on a political significance even in an area that goes beyond the two countries. Vance expressed critical views on the European institutions.'
On 14 February, during the Monaco Security Conference, the Vice-President had attacked Europe, claiming that the main threat to the Old Continent did not come from outside forces, but from the European leaders themselves, accused of undermining democratic values through repression of freedom of speech and ignoring voters' opinions on issues such as immigration. These positions were substantially shared by Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, to whom the American delegation would call for a meeting on the occasion of the official visit.
The visit to Italy of the US Vice-President, also in the light of the results obtained - and the request to meet Meloni would indicate the importance that the American administration gives to this appointment - could represent a key moment in view of a possible official journey of the premier in the USA, in the coming months, to be received to the White House.&nbsp;

